{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bc04ea70-dec0-4a36-bb4e-70ddffa7e663","content":"There's no existing pipeline in this workspace, so here's the general migration guidance:\n\n## Key changes\n\n**1. Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script)**\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform runs via `dotnet test` — VSTest@3 isn't needed.\n\n```yaml\n# Before (VSTest runner)\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After (Microsoft.Testing.Platform)\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n**2. Enable Microsoft.Testing.Platform in your test projects**\n\nIn each test `.csproj` (or in `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` bridges `dotnet test` to the new platform.\n\n**3. Publish TRX results** (unchanged)\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '**/*.trx'\n    searchFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n```\n\n**4. Publish code coverage** (unchanged)\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n> If you use the built-in .NET \"Code Coverage\" collector, the output is `.coverage` format. For Cobertura XML (needed by `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2`), switch to `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` (uses Coverlet) or add the `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` package which supports Cobertura export.\n\n## Summary of what to drop / add\n\n| Remove | Add |\n|---|---|\n| `VSTest@3` task | `DotNetCoreCLI@2` with `command: test` |\n| `codeCoverageEnabled` input | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` argument |\n| — | `EnableMSTestRunner` + `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` in csproj |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"36171ace-0cef-41b8-90d9-8be40db82c68","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There's no existing pipeline file in the repository. The user is asking a general question about how to migrate from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their Azure DevOps CI pipeline. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":781,"requestId":"E3D0:C1BFC:1B3AFFE:1E36B51:6A052049"},"id":"a8337b4d-960d-477a-98e3-0aaebbeee8ae","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:07:39.476Z","parentId":"35a35824-40dc-4250-b745-2559980bc3df"}
